{"bookmarked": 6, "bucket_name": "Today", "bucket_order": 3, "change_log": [{"anon": "stud", "data": "jdgd98zskep191", "type": "create", "uid_a": "a_0", "when": "2018-02-09T20:10:13Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "data": "jdgepplaksc4qt", "to": "jdgd98zniza190", "type": "s_answer", "uid_a": "a_1", "when": "2018-02-09T20:51:01Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "data": "jdgfh81m3cw3cn", "type": "s_answer_update", "uid_a": "a_0", "when": "2018-02-09T21:12:24Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "jdgd98zniza190", "type": "followup", "uid_a": "a_2", "when": "2018-02-09T23:21:54Z"}, {"anon": "no", "to": "jdgd98zniza190", "type": "feedback", "uid": "icdxydvnk125h8", "when": "2018-02-09T23:25:48Z"}, {"anon": "no", "data": "jdgka4wdikd4bd", "to": "jdgd98zniza190", "type": "i_answer", "uid": "icdxydvnk125h8", "when": "2018-02-09T23:26:52Z"}, {"anon": "no", "data": "jrl0cr3k7za7hp", "type": "i_answer_update", "uid": "icdxydvnk125h8", "when": "2019-01-31T19:23:45Z"}], "children": [{"bucket_name": "Today", "bucket_order": 3, "children": [], "config": {}, "created": "2018-02-09T20:51:01Z", "data": {"embed_links": []}, "folders": [], "history": [{"anon": "stud", "content": "<p>Nope that&#39;s not true. Look <a href=\"http://guide.berkeley.edu/undergraduate/degree-programs/electrical-engineering-computer-sciences/#minorrequirementstext\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>\u00a0. Try googling next time.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>---</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>^That&#39;s what I thought too, then I saw this declaration form on the EECS minor site (<a href=\"https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/minor\">https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/minor</a>):</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://berkeley.app.box.com/s/cxr67xfrprany6z9k8577bbakk0rum1w\">https://berkeley.app.box.com/s/cxr67xfrprany6z9k8577bbakk0rum1w</a></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>It says &#34;a\u00a0minimum overall GPA of 3.00 is required at the time this form is submitted.&#34; Am I misunderstanding something? An instructor confirmation would be very helpful. Thanks.</p>", "created": "2018-02-09T21:12:24Z", "subject": "", "uid_a": "a_0"}, {"anon": "stud", "content": "<p>Nope that&#39;s not true. Look <a href=\"http://guide.berkeley.edu/undergraduate/degree-programs/electrical-engineering-computer-sciences/#minorrequirementstext\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>\u00a0. Try googling next time.</p>", "created": "2018-02-09T20:51:01Z", "subject": "", "uid_a": "a_1"}], "id": "jdgeppl32ec4qs", "is_tag_endorse": false, "tag_endorse": [], "tag_endorse_arr": [], "type": "s_answer"}, {"anon": "stud", "bucket_name": "Week 2/4 - 2/10", "bucket_order": 116, "children": [{"anon": "no", "bucket_name": "Week 2/4 - 2/10", "bucket_order": 116, "children": [], "config": {}, "created": "2018-02-09T23:25:48Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "jdgk8rchpwt38v", "subject": "<p>Yes, absolutely. Minors are not constrained by College.\u00a0</p>", "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "type": "feedback", "uid": "icdxydvnk125h8", "updated": "2018-02-09T23:25:48Z"}], "config": {}, "created": "2018-02-09T23:21:54Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "jdgk3r9v3uj1ny", "no_answer": 0, "no_upvotes": 0, "subject": "<p>is it possible to have eecs minor though i&#39;m L&amp;S student majoring in stats?</p>", "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "type": "followup", "uid_a": "a_2", "updated": "2018-02-09T23:21:54Z"}, {"bucket_name": "Today", "bucket_order": 3, "children": [], "config": {}, "created": "2018-02-09T23:26:52Z", "data": {"embed_links": []}, "folders": [], "history": [{"anon": "no", "content": "<p></p>", "created": "2019-01-31T19:23:45Z", "subject": "", "uid": "icdxydvnk125h8"}, {"anon": "no", "content": "<p>The policy\u00a0<em>was</em> that students need a 3.0 to declare the minor, and a 2.0 to graduate from it. Because of that discrepancy, the Vice Chair has approved exceptions for students not quite at a 3.0 GPA. I would still submit application, but expect a delayed response.\u00a0</p>", "created": "2018-02-09T23:26:52Z", "subject": "", "uid": "icdxydvnk125h8"}], "id": "jdgka4wbyh44bc", "is_tag_endorse": false, "tag_endorse": [{"admin": false, "endorser": {"hyq0br1u3kx7dg": 1}, "facebook_id": null, "id": "hz4uczhrpbq164", "name": "Woo Sik (Lewis) Kim", "photo": null, "photo_url": null, "published": true, "role": "student", "us": false}], "tag_endorse_arr": ["hz4uczhrpbq164"], "type": "i_answer"}], "config": {}, "created": "2018-02-09T20:10:13Z", "data": {"embed_links": []}, "default_anonymity": "no", "drafts": null, "folders": ["other", "faculty_advising"], "history": [{"anon": "stud", "content": "<p>I&#39;ve heard that to declare an EECS minor, you need to have a 3.0 cumulative. Is this true? If so, how &#34;strict&#34; is that requirement? Thank you.</p>", "created": "2018-02-09T20:10:13Z", "subject": "EECS Minor - requires 3.0 cumulative?", "uid_a": "a_0"}], "i_edits": [], "id": "jdgd98zniza190", "is_bookmarked": false, "is_tag_good": false, "my_favorite": false, "no_answer": 0, "no_answer_followup": 0, "nr": 6222, "num_favorites": 1, "q_edits": [], "request_instructor": 0, "request_instructor_me": false, "s_edits": [], "status": "active", "t": 1654550142514, "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "tags": ["faculty_advising", "other", "student"], "type": "question", "unique_views": 387}